A Young Nigerian lawyer, Femi Gbede has been named one of the top 40 black lawyers under 40. He earned the recognition because of his legal SUCCESS AND PROFESSIONAL REPUTATION in New York, United States of America. Gbede, an Investment Funds Attorney at THE NEW YORK OFFICE OF an ELITE INTERNATIONAL LAW FIRM, Fried Frank, advises on the structuring and offering of private investment funds and other alternative investment vehicles. His practice focuses on all aspects of fund formation and other highly complex transactions. An alumnus of the New York University School of Law and Cambridge University, FEMI was  the recipient of the Outstanding Young Lawyer of the Year award at the 2021 ESQ Nigerian Legal Awards. “We are excited to welcome Femi as part of The National Black Lawyers Top 40 Under 40!” The organisers wrote in  their  newsletter.